                            <entry>
                    <title>The history of &quot;Taking Baby Steps&quot;</title>
                    <link rel="alternate" href="http://coderetreat.org/xn/detail/6456126:BlogPost:21111"/>
                                        <id>tag:coderetreat.org,2013-01-16:6456126:BlogPost:21111</id>
                                        <updated>2013-01-16T21:00:00.000Z</updated>
                    
                                            <author>
                            <name>Adi Bolboaca</name>
                            <uri>http://coderetreat.org/profile/adibolb</uri>
                        </author>
                    
                    <summary type="html">
                        &lt;p&gt;Let me tell you a story on how I thought about teaching other programmers how to take small steps to help them minimize the mistakes by focusing on a small thought.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A couple of years ago I was working on a legacy project, meaning I did not know anything about the business, and it was written in Delphi .Net which was totally unknown to me. I needed to translate this medium-sized code-base from Delphi .Net into .Net / Silverlight.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All the team was using a centralized source…&lt;/p&gt;                    </summary>

                    <content type="html">
&lt;p&gt;Let me tell you a story on how I thought about teaching other programmers how to take small steps to help them minimize the mistakes by focusing on a small thought.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A couple of years ago I was working on a legacy project, meaning I did not know anything about the business, and it was written in Delphi .Net which was totally unknown to me. I needed to translate this medium-sized code-base from Delphi .Net into .Net / Silverlight.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All the team was using a centralized source control system, namely TFS. But I needed to be sure that the steps I take are safe in my routine of translating the code from Delphi .Net to Silverlight, so I put in place Git. It helped me ensure that the steps I do locally are the good ones. I had done this before, using Git or SVN as a local source control while my team was using SVN as a centralized repository for the source code.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can read more on my blog: &lt;a href=&quot;http://blog.adrianbolboaca.ro/2013/01/the-history-of-taking-baby-steps/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;The history of &quot;Taking Baby Steps&quot;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
